.TH STUBLOAD "1" "1 April 2024" "" ""

.SH "NAME"
stubload \- manual page for stubload

.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.B stubload
.RB [ "\-hvViCARlcr" ]
.RB [ "\-n[#]" ]
.RB [ "\-\-force" ]
.RB [ "\-\-verbose" ]

.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.B stubload
is a shell script that simplifies
the process of creating, removing and modifying
Linux EFIstub entries using efibootmgr

.SH "OPTIONS"
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
print help & exit
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
don't suppress efibootmgr's and other utilities output
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
print version of stubload, efibootmgr and bash
.TP
\fB\-i\fR, \fB\-\-prompt\fR
prompt before performing potentially dangerous actions
.TP
\fB\-C\fR, \fB\-\-edit_config\fR
edit configuration file located at
/etc/efistub/stubload.conf
.TP
\fB\-A\fR, \fB\-\-add_cmdline\fR
add option to kernel cmdline (global by default,
use '-n' to select entry)
.TP
\fB\-R\fR, \fB\-\-rm_cmdline\fR
remove option from kernel cmdline
.TP
\fB\-l\fR, \fB\-\-list\fR
list entries created by stubload
.TP
\fB\-c\fR, \fB\-\-create\fR
create entries with efibootmgr
.TP
\fB\-r\fR, \fB\-\-remove\fR
remove entries
.TP
\fB\-\-force\fR
stop errors from exiting
.TP
\fB\-\-config\fR [file]
specify configuration file
.TP
\fB\-n\fR[#]
specify entrys number to target

.SH "EXAMPLES"
\fR
.SS "Create entry 1 and 2:"
\fR
.nf
.B
# stubload -n1 -n2 -c
create: Entry 1
create: Entry 2
.fi
\fR
.SS "List entries created by stubload with cmdlines:"
\fR
.nf
.B
# stubload -lv
0000|1 Entry 1
 vmlinuz root=/dev/root ro quiet nosplash
0001|2 Entry 2
 vmlinuz root=/dev/root ro quiet nosplash
.fi
\fR
.SS "Add fbcon=nodefer to cmdline for entry 1 and 2:"
\fR
.nf
.B
# stubload -n1 -n2 -A "fbcon=nodefer"
fbcon=nodefer: Added to cmdline
fbcon=nodefer: Added to cmdline
.fi

.SH "SEE ALSO"
The Git repository for
stubload
is maintained at
.BR <https://github.com/alemontn/stubload>
.TP
You can report issues or ask questions there
